1. Create github testing project
2. learn how to use GIT, 1 HOUR TRAINing : 
    - How to clone
    - How to create a branch
    - How to commit
    - How to push
    - How to create a pull request
    - How to resolve a conflict

1. Create project :
    1. Frontend project : 
        - VueJs 3
        - Typescript
        - Eslint
        - Tailwind CSS
        - Vuetify
        - Vue Router
        - vite
        - pinia
    2. Backend project :
        - .Net 10
        - entity framework
        - fluent validator
        - swagger
        - Clean architecture :
            - API project
                - Controllers : This will contain the API endpoints
                    - It'll consume the Application project to execute the commands and queries
                - Middlewares : Exception handling, Logging, Authentication, Authorization
            - Application project
                - Commands: This will contain the Writing operations (Create, Update, Delete)
                - Queries : This will contain the Reading operations (GetAll, GetById)
            - Domain project:
                - Entities : This will contain the business entities (User, Product, Order, etc.)
                - Enums : This will contain the enums (UserRole, OrderStatus, etc.)
            - Infrastructure project :
                - Make sure to paginate DATA
                - Repositories -> access to DBCONTEXT
                    - Example: 
                        - UserRepository : IGenericRepository<User>
                    - IGenericRepository<T> : 
                        - GetAll() XXX
                        - GetById()
                        - Add()
                        - Update()
                        - Delete()


2. 
1. Create the initial user management
    1. Create User entity in the Domain project
    2. Create User Migration
    2. Create UserRepository in the Infrastructure project
    3. Create User commands and queries 
    4. Create User management Controller

2. Create basic authentication system 
    1. A user can register to the application
    2. A user can login to the application
    3. A user can reset his password

3. Implement RBAC (Role Based Acces Control)
    1. Create Roles 
    2. Create Permissions - Static permissions injected into the database using a migration 
        - The permissions will be in this format : EntityName.Operation, 
                - Example : User.Create, User.Update, User.Delete ...
    3. A user can have many Roles, A user Can have many permissions | A role can have many permissions
    4. Create Apis/Services to manage roles and permissions
    5. Add a middleware to manage user authorization/authontication, 
        - i a user doesn't have a specific permission return 403, if he's not authenticated return 401
        - Permissions must be set in the controller methods, using a special attribute 


Class diagrams: 
```mermaid
classDiagram
    class User {
        +Guid Id
        +string Username
        +string FirstName
        +string LastName
        +string Email
        +string PasswordHash
        +Date DateOfBirth
        +string PhoneNumber
        +string Address
        +List<Role> Roles
        +List<Permission> Permissions
    }

    class Role {
        +Guid Id
        +string Name
        +List<Permission> Permissions
    }

    class Permission {
        +Guid Id
        +string Name
    }

    class RolePermission {
        +Guid RoleId
        +Guid PermissionId
    }

    class UserRole {
        +Guid UserId
        +Guid RoleId
    }

    class UserPermission {
        +Guid UserId
        +Guid PermissionId
    }

    User "*" -- "*" Role : has
    Role "*" -- "*" Permission : has
    User "*" -- "*" Permission : has
```